node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Astronomy Daily on September 13, 2021 tagging @thom_astro. May be an image of nature and sky.

node.text:
Red, green and blue in this aurora picture!
.
Quote "The green is the standard aurora colour. Aurora turn red at higher altitudes as the solar winds excite atomic atoms to give off different light. The blue is from an impending sunrise on the horizon. When the sun comes, the aurora goes away, or at least is not visible anymore!"
.
Photo via @thom_astro
.
Tag @the.astronomy.daily to feature your photos!
